<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Right now the common variant to include jQuery UI CSS is to add:
$view-&gt;JQuery()-&gt;addStylesheet('/path/to/the.css');</p>

<p>When jQuery is enabled - it will be rendered (outputed inside
head tag). But as I want to add UI CSS style, it would be better
to include it ONLY when UI is enbled.</p>

<p>So I propose to add addUIStylesheet($path) method to add stylesheets
which will be outputed only when UI will be enabled.</p>

